          <li><strong>Males</strong> tend to be more frequent talkers and may develop a wider vocabulary faster.</li>
          <li><strong>Females</strong> can be slightly quieter but may develop clearer, more deliberate speech patterns.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>🚀 <strong>Fun Fact:</strong> African Grey parrots can understand the context in conversations, making them one of the most intelligent talking birds in the world!</p>
      </div>
    </section>

